article.headline: Sacramento State 79, Denver 65
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Jason Harris scored 22 points and DaShawn Freeman added 21 to lead Sacramento State to a 79-65 victory over Denver on Thursday night. Harris added 10 rebounds and Alex Bausley scored 12 points for the Hornets (9-5), who bounced back from a 30-point loss at UCLA to improve to 5-0 at home. Sacramento State has won eight of 11 and has not lost consecutive games this season. Yemi Nicholson had 23 points and 14 rebounds to lead Denver (5-6), which wrapped up an 0-5 road trip. Andrew Carpenter added 16 points. This marked the first meeting ever between the Hornets and Pioneers.
